{
  "id": 5182756304846848,
  "name": "Stricter *+json MIME token validation for JSON modules",
  "summary": "Reject JSON module script responses whose MIME type’s type or subtype contains non‑HTTP token code points (e.g. spaces) when matched via *+json; aligns with MIME Sniffing spec and other engines. This change is part of the Interop2025 modules focus area.\n\nRelated Issues: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=297161\nRelated PR: https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt/pull/54219\n\nDraft CL: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/6931461",
